[90mThat's your problem. The subscriptions exist but they weren't attached to your app version when you submitted. Here's how to fix it:[39m
[90m[39m
[90mGo to your iOS 1.0 version page (click on "1.0 Rejected" in the left sidebar or go to App Store → your version)[39m
[90mScroll down to the "In-App Purchases and Subscriptions" section on that page[39m
[90mClick the "+" button to select your subscriptions[39m
[90mAdd both Premium Monthly and Premium Annual[39m
[90mSave[39m
[90mThis is the step that connects the subscription products to your app submission so Apple's reviewer can actually test them. Without this, the reviewer saw a paywall with no purchasable products — which is exactly what triggered both 2.1.0 and 3.1.2.[39m
